imedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f9/Mount_Hood_Highway%2C_Oregon.jpg","cap":", Oregon","desc":"Mount Hood Highway, Oregon, USA","credit":"en:User:Kkmd · CC BY-SA 3.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mount_Hood_Highway,_Oregon.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/White_River_at_Mount_Hood_Highway.jpg/1280px-White_River_at_Mount_Hood_Highway.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d8/White_River_at_Mount_Hood_Highway.jpg","cap":"White River at","desc":"The White River, near Mount Hood, Oregon, USA.","credit":"AlexAH · CC BY 3.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:White_River_at_Mount_Hood_Highway.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f7/Mount_Hood_Oregon_%2828652454814%29.jpg/1280px-Mount_Hood_Oregon_%2828652454814%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f7/Mount_Hood_Oregon_%2828652454814%29.jpg","cap":"Mount Hood Oregon (28652454814)","desc":"Mt. Hood as seen from US Highway 26 in Rhododendron, Oregon.","credit":"Tony Webster from Minneapolis, Minnesota · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mount_Hood_Oregon_(28652454814).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/Mount_Hood_Highway%2C_OR_9-1-13e_%289723295103%29.jpg/1280px-Mount_Hood_Highway%2C_OR_9-1-13e_%289723295103%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/eb/Mount_Hood_Highway%2C_OR_9-1-13e_%289723295103%29.jpg","cap":", OR 9 1 13e (9723295103)","desc":"(1 in a multiple picture set) Mount Hood is a beautiful 45-minute drive southeast of Portland, OR. This is a view from the Mount Hood Highway. The last 15 minutes of the drive offer many great views of the peak, the highest in Oregon.","credit":"inkknife_2000 (7.5 million views +) · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mount_Hood_Highway,_OR_9-1-13e_(9723295103).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/Waterfall%2C_Mount_Hood%2C_OR_9-1-13t_%289723292073%29.jpg/1280px-Waterfall%2C_Mount_Hood%2C_OR_9-1-13t_%289723292073%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/3a/Waterfall%2C_Mount_Hood%2C_OR_9-1-13t_%289723292073%29.jpg","cap":"Waterfall, Mount Hood, OR 9 1 13t (9723292073)","desc":"(1 in a multiple picture set) Along the Mt. Hood Highway you will see a couple of these waterfalls coming out of the side of the hill. I'm thinking they are spring fed. This one runs right under the highway.","credit":"inkknife_2000 (7.5 million views +) · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Waterfall,_Mount_Hood,_OR_9-1-13t_(9723292073).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Mount_Hood_Highway%2C_OR_9-13_%2814659820238%29.jpg/1280px-Mount_Hood_Highway%2C_OR_9-13_%2814659820238%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5e/Mount_Hood_Highway%2C_OR_9-13_%2814659820238%29.jpg","cap":", OR 9 13 (14659820238)","desc":"(1 in a multiple picture album) I got up early on a Sunday and drove from Gresham, OR to Mt. Hood on the highway named for this monster mountain. There wasn't much traffic and as I got closer to the volcano, every turn held a view.","credit":"inkknife_2000 (7.5 million views +) · CC BY-SA 2.0","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mount_Hood_Highway,_OR_9-13_(14659820238).jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Mount_Hood_Tree_Line%2C_OR_8-13_%2816171629489%29.jpg/1280px-Mount_Hood_Tree_Line%2C_OR_8-13_%2816171629489%29.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e3/Mount_Hood_Tree_Line%2C_OR_8-13_%2816171629489%29.jpg","cap":"Mount Hood Tree Line, OR 8 13 (16171629489)","desc":"(1 in a multiple picture album) Climbing on the south slope of Mt. Hood in Oregon, we've reached the tree line. Ahead is just rock. You can see several glaciers in this picture. Also note the wild flowersl","cre